Next Steps - Configure Talos with Ansible:

  1. Navigate to Ansible Talos directory:
     cd ../../ansible/talos

  2. Generate Talos machine configurations:
     make generate-configs

     This creates configs in ansible/talos/configs/:
       • secrets.yaml (cluster PKI)
       • controlplane.yaml (CP machine config)
       • worker.yaml (worker machine config)
       • talosconfig (Talos API credentials)

  3. Apply configurations to nodes (VMs will be started):
     make apply-configs

  4. Bootstrap Kubernetes cluster:
     make bootstrap

  5. Verify cluster health:
     make verify

  6. Access the cluster:
     export KUBECONFIG=$(pwd)/configs/kubeconfig
     kubectl get nodes

